These skill playbooks were originally vendored from cogmemory's
docs/llm/skills/, but the cogmemory standalone daemon was retired
2026-06-12 (Phase 6 of the fold; tagged v1.0.0-archived). ytsejam is
now the canonical home — edit these files in place; there is no
upstream to sync back to.

Propagation note: SkillsStore.seed() (server/src/skills.ts) copies
seeds into the runtime data dir with COPYFILE_EXCL — copy-if-missing
only. Editing this seed does NOT update an already-seeded live copy
at ~/.ytsejam/data/skills/<name>.md.

To activate a seed change on a running instance:

  bash deploy/sync-skills.sh --yes   # copy seeds → live for drifted skills

deploy/deploy.sh runs scripts/check-skills-drift.sh between build and
symlink-swap; a release that has not been synced will abort the deploy.
See docs/agents/skills.md "Drift gate (deploy-time)" for the full contract.

This file has no .md extension on purpose: the skills store seeds
and lists only *.md files.
